{#
 The chrome's ONE inline-SVG wrapper, server side. Every icon the templates draw is the same 24x24
 stroked outline and differs only in its path data, but the wrapper was written out at each call
 site — header.ut's rail toggle plus search/appearance/logout — so `stroke-width` and the two
 linecap attributes were four independent copies of a value that is meant to make one icon SET.
 fs-widgets.js's svgIcon() is the same wrapper for the icons the JS builds; the two are the server
 and client halves of one look.

 `body` is the shape, and it is emitted RAW on purpose: it is author-written markup from the caller
 (paths and circles), never anything a request can influence, and `{{ }}` in a ucode template does
 not escape — escaping here would print the path data as visible text. `cls` is optional and
 defaults to the icon class every chrome control uses.

 aria-hidden: each of these sits beside its own label (or in a control that carries one), and an
 unlabelled <svg> would otherwise be announced as a graphic in its own right.
 Licensed to the public under the Apache License 2.0.
-#}
<svg class="{{ cls ?? 'fs-ico' }}" aria-hidden="true" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.9" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">{{ body }}</svg>
